enter into the brotherhood that is the Champions of Avendar.  This is not a
simple decision, but rather one I have contemplated for many months now. 
However, I feel that it is right for me to do.  

Firstly, I would like to tell you about who I am, and why I have chosen this
course of action.  I am, of course, Aeli Iristae.  I was the only daughter
of my mother, Tyrali.  Unfortunately, my mother went away before I could
remember, so my grandmother says.  I am noble born, but it has done little
for me in my lifetime, especially since I left home to take up my studies as
a psion.  I have met many people during my lifetime, but few have had more
impact than Brachaormaul and Rulan.  I was awed by Brachaormaul's prowess
and zealous attitude, which first drew me to the tower.  After meeting
Rulan, I knew for certain that this was the right decision.  

I never really considered myself a violent person.  I try to make myself
affable, and easily approachable.  It seems to work, for many speak to me
without misapprehension.  I don't believe that violence is the answer, for
in death lies more problems.  I try my hardest to find a mutually agreeable
way out of a situation, but sometimes that can fail.  However, should
justice be metered out, I do not hesitate when force is required.  

I hope to see, during my lifetime, the influence of the Champions of Avendar
expanded.  There are many who simply have no need for the light or its
teachings, and that is something I wish to change.  In the light, lies true
hapiness, something many people strive to attain, but have not been shown
the way.  If given the opportunity, I would not mind the attempt to spread
the word of Jolinn, whom I am completely dedicated to.  I try to do as much
already, and will continue to do so.  

